            "id": "99a92a99a3504b61aff7c",
            "questionText": "A sedan with a mass of $!$1200 \\text{ kg}$!$ traveling at $!$15 \\text{ m/s}$!$ collides head-on with an SUV of mass $!$2000 \\text{ kg}$!$ moving at $!$10 \\text{ m/s}$!$ in the opposite direction. After the collision, the vehicles become entangled and move together as a single unit. If the crumple zones in the sedan extend the collision time to $!$0.25 \\text{ s}$!$, calculate the magnitude of the average force exerted on the sedan during the collision.",
