        {
            "id": "d5b8f83731d04823aa1c1",
            "questionText": "A massive rocket launches from Earth, expelling hot gases downwards to generate thrust. The rocket has an initial total mass of $!$50000 \\text{ kg}$!$. It expels gases at a constant rate of $!$500 \\text{ kg/s}$!$ relative to the rocket, with an exhaust velocity of $!$2000 \\text{ m/s}$!$ downwards relative to the rocket. Calculate the magnitude of the average resultant force (thrust) exerted on the rocket during the first $!$1.0 \\text{ s}$!$ of its launch. Assume the change in the rocket's mass during this short interval is negligible for simplifying the resultant force calculation.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
